# SC2086: Double quote to prevent globbing/splitting — intentional in sed
#         substitutions where the variable is a controlled path
# SC2015: A && B || C is not if-then-else — used intentionally for fallbacks
# SC2034: Variable appears unused — some vars are used by sourced/eval'd code
# SC2320: Redirect masking exit code — intentional in shift 2>/dev/null || true
# SC2029: SSH commands intentionally expand variables client-side
# SC2016: Single-quoted strings with $ are intentional in sed/test assertions
# SC1090: Non-constant source — used for dynamic config sourcing
# SC2154: Variables set by dialog/sourced files, not visible to ShellCheck
disable=SC2086,SC2015,SC2034,SC2320,SC2029,SC2016,SC1090,SC2154
